												<div class="vers-no">8</div>
						<div class="vers-content">It was in Azariasâ€™ thirty-eighth year that Jeroboamâ€™s son Zacharias began his reign in Samaria; it lasted six months.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers154332" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">9</div>
						<div class="vers-content">He defied the Lordâ€™s will, like his fathers before him, and would not forgo the sins of Jeroboam, son of Nabat, that taught Israel to sin.</div>
					</div>
