												<div class="vers-no">19</div>
						<div class="vers-content">the country suffered invasion by Phul, king of Assyria, and Menahem paid him a thousand talents of silver, to win support for his claim to the throne.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers154343" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">20</div>
						<div class="vers-content">To find this tribute for the Assyrian king, Menahem imposed a tax of fifty silver pieces on all the rich and powerful men in his kingdom. Thus the Assyrian king was induced to go home and rid the country of his presence.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers154344" class="vers">
